p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{4}{7} + \frac{13}{14}
        \amp = \frac{8}{14} + \frac{13}{14} \\
        \amp = \frac{8 + 13}{14} \\
        \amp = \frac{21}{14} \amp  \hbox{We can reduce this by dividing 7 into both the numerator and the denominator.}\\
        \amp = \frac{3}{2}
\end{aligned}
    }
